<paragraph blockId="54.[151,1058,1526,1577]" pageId="54" pageNumber="1013">
E t y m o l o g y: The trivial name, 
<emphasis box="[554,647,1527,1548]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="1013">convexus</emphasis>
, is a Latin name with the meaning of &quot;arched&quot;; with reference to the very convex pronotal disc.
</paragraph>
